<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>12721</id>
    <title>Distorted company logo in Like Box</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">When the Like Box is rendered in IE 6 &amp; 7_ our company logo (LeapFrog) is distorted.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">For some reason it is being sized to 50px W x 40px H_ whereas the other PC-based browsers and the Mac-based browsers correctly display the logo at 50 x 50.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">I ve tried different widths and heights for the iFrame_ but this hasn t affected the dimensions of the logo within.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">How can I fix this?</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">This is the actual code I m using for the Like Box iframe:</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">&lt;iframe id= hdrFB  src= http://www.facebook.com/plugins/likebox.php?href=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.facebook.com%2FLeapFrog&amp;amp;width=206&amp;amp;connections=0&amp;amp;stream=false&amp;amp;header=false&amp;amp;height=62  scrolling= no  frameborder= 0  style= border:none;overflow:hidden;width:206px;height:62px;_width:170px;_height:75px;*border:1px solid #dddddd;filter:progid:DXImageTransform.Microsoft.Shadow(color=#999999_strength=2_direction=150);  allowTransparency= true &gt;&lt;/iframe&gt;</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">The distortion will happen regardless of the settings chosen.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">You can see for yourself by entering  http://www.facebook.com/leapfrog  as the Facebook Page URL here - http://developers.facebook.com/docs/reference/plugins/like-box</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
